# RapidAid Ambulance Dashboard UI Design

## Purpose

The Ambulance Dashboard enables ambulance drivers to receive emergency requests, navigate to patients, communicate with hospitals, and update the emergency status in real time.

## Page Layout

### Header

- 🚑 RapidAid Logo
- Dashboard
- Emergency Requests
- Navigation
- Notifications
- Profile

## Driver Information

Display:

- Driver Name
- Ambulance Number
- Current Status
- Current Location
- Shift Status

---

## Emergency Request Card

Display:

- Request ID
- Patient Name
- Emergency Type
- Severity Level
- Patient Location
- Distance
- Estimated Arrival Time (ETA)

Buttons:

- Accept Request
- Reject Request

---

## Live Navigation

Features:

- Live GPS Map
- Fastest Route
- Traffic Updates
- Alternate Route
- Distance Remaining
- ETA

---

## Patient Information

Display:

- Name
- Age
- Blood Group
- Medical Conditions
- Allergies
- Emergency Contact

---

## Hospital Information

Display:

- Assigned Hospital
- Distance
- ICU Availability
- Emergency Department
- Contact Number

---

## Status Update Buttons

- 🚑 On the Way
- 📍 Arrived at Patient
- 👤 Patient On Board
- 🏥 Arrived at Hospital
- ✅ Case Completed

---

## Communication

Quick Actions:

- Call Patient
- Call Hospital
- Call Emergency Contact
- Send Status Update

---

## Notifications

Examples:

- New Emergency Assigned
- Hospital Changed
- Route Updated
- Traffic Alert

---

## Performance Summary

Display:

- Today's Completed Trips
- Average Response Time
- Total Distance Covered
- Driver Rating

---

